          "alt": "Abstract Login and Registration User Flow"
        }}></img></a></p>
    <p>{`The exact data being fetched and the step `}<em parentName="p">{`"Processes Login / Registration
Info"`}</em>{` depend, of course, on the actual Strategy being used. But it is important
to understand that `}<strong parentName="p">{`"Your Application"`}</strong>{` is responsible for rendering the
actual Login and Registration HTML Forms. You can of course implement one app
for rendering all the Login, Registration, ... screens, and another app (think
"Service Oriented Architecture", "Micro-Services" or "Service Mesh") is
responsible for rendering your Dashboards, Management Screens, and so on.`}</p>
