    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`The `}<strong parentName="li">{`Login/Registration User Flow`}</strong>{` is initiated because a link was clicked
or an action was performed that requires an active user session.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`ORY Kratos executes Jobs defined in the `}<strong parentName="li">{`Before Login/Registration
Workflow`}</strong>{`. If a failure occurs, the whole flow is aborted.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`The user's browser is redirected to
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`http://127.0.0.1:4455/.ory/kratos/public/self-service/browser/flows/requests/(login|registration)`}</inlineCode>{`
(the notation `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`(login|registration)`}</inlineCode>{` expresses the two possibilities of
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`../self-service/browser/flows/requests/login`}</inlineCode>{` or
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`../self-service/browser/flows/requests/registration`}</inlineCode>{`).`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`ORY Kratos does some internal processing (e.g. checks if a session cookie is
set, generates payloads for form fields, sets CSRF token, ...) and redirects
the user's browser to the Login UI URL which is defined using the
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`urls.login_ui`}</inlineCode>{` (or `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`urls.registration_ui`}</inlineCode>{`) config or `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`URLS_LOGIN_UI`}</inlineCode>{` (or
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`URLS_REGISTRATION_UI`}</inlineCode>{`) environment variable, which is set to the ui
endpoints - for example `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`https://127.0.0.1:4455/auth/login`}</inlineCode>{` and
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`https://127.0.0.1:4455/auth/registration`}</inlineCode>{`). The user's browser is thus
redirected to
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`https://127.0.0.1:4455/auth/(login|registration)?request=abcde`}</inlineCode>{`. The
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`request`}</inlineCode>{` query parameter includes a unique ID which will be used to fetch
contextual data for this login request.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Your Server-Side Application makes a `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`GET`}</inlineCode>{` request to
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`http://kratos:4434/self-service/browser/flows/requests/(login|registration)?request=abcde`}</inlineCode>{`.
ORY Kratos responds with a JSON Payload that contains data (form fields,
error messages, ...) for all enabled User Login Strategies:`}<pre parentName="li"><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-json5"
          }}>{`{
  id: 'abcde',
  methods: {
    password: { method: 'password', config: { action: '...', fields: [] } },
    oidc: { method: 'oidc', config: { action: '...', fields: [] } },
  },
}
`}</code></pre></li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Your Server-Side applications renders the data however you see fit. The User
interacts with it an completes the Login by clicking, for example, the
"Login", the "Login with Google", ... button.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`The User's browser makes a request to one of ORY Kratos' Strategy URLs (e.g.
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`http://127.0.0.1:4455/.ory/kratos/public/self-service/browser/strategies/password/(login|registration)`}</inlineCode>{`
or
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`https://127.0.0.1:4455/.ory/kratos/public/self-service/browser/strategies/oidc/auth/abcde`}</inlineCode>{`).
ORY Kratos validates the User's credentials (when logging in - e.g. Username
and Password, by performing an OpenID Connect flow, ...) or the registration
form data (when signing up - e.g. is the E-Mail address valid, is the person
at least 21 years old, ...):`}<ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul">{`If the credentials / form data is invalid, the Login Request's JSON Payload
is updated - for example with`}<pre parentName="li"><code parentName="pre" {...{
                "className": "language-json5"
              }}>{`{
  id: 'abcde',
  methods: {
    oidc: {
      method: 'oidc',
      config: {
        /* ... */
      },
    },
    password: {
      method: 'password',
      config: {
        /* ... */
        errors: [
          {
            message: 'The provided credentials are invalid. Check for spelling mistakes in your password or username, email address, or phone number.',
          },
        ],
      },
    },
  },
}
`}</code></pre>{`and the user's Browser is redirected back to the Login UI:
`}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`https://127.0.0.1:4455/auth/(login|registration)?request=abcde`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</li>
          <li parentName="ul">{`If credentials / data is valid, ORY Kratos proceeds with the next step.`}</li>
          <li parentName="ul">{`If the flow is a registration request and the registration data is valid,
the identity is created.`}</li>
        </ul></li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`ORY Kratos executes hooks defined in the `}<strong parentName="li">{`After Login/Registration Hooks`}</strong>{`.
If a failure occurs, the whole flow is aborted.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`The client receives the expected response. For browsers, this is a HTTP
Redirection, for API clients it will be a JSON response containing the
session and/or identity. For more information on this topic check
`}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "/kratos/docs/next/concepts/selfservice-flow-completion"
        }}>{`Self-Service Flow Completion`}</a>{`.`}</li>
    </ol>
